title: Judge warns JPMorgan Chase of contempt finding for slow-walking evidence in Jeffrey Epstein case
description: JPMorgan is accused in lawsuits of enabling sex trafficking by Jeffrey Epstein, a former friend of Donald Trump and Bill Clinton who killed himself in 2019.

title: 'I got a check the other day for $8': TV and film writers share why they're on strike
description: TV and film writers are striking after contract negotiations stalled. Their complaints are bigger than pay. “It is about a systemic problem,” they say.

title: McDonald’s new battle over the way the Big Mac and fries are packaged
description: McDonald’s is making some progress on use of recycled and renewable packaging, but environmental activists want the fast food chain to do more with reusables.

title: Recycling 'end-of-life' solar panels, wind turbines, is about to be climate tech's big waste business
description: Solar panels, wind turbines and electric vehicles are all becoming more common. So too is the waste when climate technology reaches the end of its life cycle.

title: Google staffers praise engineers for I/O, poke fun at execs because they 'just kept saying A.I.'
description: Google shares jumped after the company's developer conference this week, and employees were quick to give the credit to engineers.

title: Airlines are offering more U.S.-Europe service than ever — but don't expect bargains
description: Airlines are flying the highest number of seats between the U.S. and Europe in more than four years.
